                      Human stories through music and dance                    British Council and ICCR present In the Further Soil, a dance-and-music theatre production that tells the story of urban landscapes of India and the UK. Inspired by the works of Tagore, it explores the emergence of contemporary British Asian dance and music forms in the UK and their relation to their traditional roots in India. It has been developed through a collaboration of international artistes from the UK and India, through experimentation, skill-sharing and artistic exploration. Direction: Harmage Singh Kalirai. Produced by Sampad (Birmingham, UK) and Teamwork Productions (India).            Event: Dance-and-music theatre presentation by young artistes of India and UK When: Today 6.30 pm Where: Rabindranath Tagore Centre, ICCR, 9A Ho Chi Minh Sarani	                    
